        <name>1.4.1.5 Cancelling Common Factors</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;h4 class="HELM_example"&gt;Example&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Simplify \(\dfrac{3x+6}{6x+12}\)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 class="HELM_solution"&gt;Solution&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First we factorise the numerator and the denominator to see if there are any common factors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(\qquad \dfrac{3x+6}{6x+12} = \dfrac{3(x+2)}{6(x+2)} = \dfrac{3}{6} = \dfrac{1}{2}\)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The factors \(x + 2\) and 3 have been cancelled.&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
